{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f20e77e7-3268-4879-a6a9-18756ada6e0c","content":"Here's what to change:\n\n1. **Update the adapter** — upgrade `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **4.6.0+** (you already have this).\n\n2. **Add the platform package**:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\" Version=\"1.5.3\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable the new platform** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Remove** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` — it's the VSTest entry point and is replaced by the new platform.\n\n5. **Run tests** with `dotnet test` as usual — the new platform is now the host.\n\n**Optional but recommended:**\n- Add `<EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>` if you want the test project to be a self-contained executable.\n- Add `<OutputType>Exe</OutputType>` alongside the runner setting.\n\n> **Note:** NUnit3TestAdapter 4.6.0 added Microsoft.Testing.Platform support. If you hit issues, check for the latest 4.6.x patch.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"47caa4a6-bf01-44b0-945c-e10d25f7ad12","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing infrastructure, not a code task. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":369,"requestId":"0C08:3A1531:1E6E18:23AA8E:69F00429"},"id":"1e71f2ea-75eb-4e88-a75b-ce54156b8b3c","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:49:54.542Z","parentId":"b74279e2-399f-4eec-88e1-589b523d99c4"}
